# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Smart Door Lock App – Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values for your environment.
# Variables prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ are inlined by the Expo bundler and
# are therefore visible to the app at runtime (do not put secrets here).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Backend REST/WebSocket API base URL.
#
# • Production (cloud):
#     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://smart-doorlock-server-851342133148.europe-west1.run.app/
#
# • Local development (replace with your machine's LAN IP):
#     EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.x.x:8000/
#
# IMPORTANT: when testing on a physical device, use your computer's local
# network IP (not "localhost" or "127.0.0.1") so the phone can reach the
# server.  Run `ipconfig` (Windows) or `ifconfig` / `ip a` (macOS/Linux) to
# find your IP.
#
# Leave blank to use the production cloud server (default fallback).
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=
